						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">yaazz wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">So the hardware evaluates the attributes and indexes as y coordinates? why would it do this?</div>
<br />This happens only in the case that all eight sprite slots are filled. It appears Nintendo and Ricoh didn't thoroughly test the obscure feature of 9th sprite detection. Why? I'm guessing they didn't require it to be perfectly accurate, just a debugging aid, and possibly even something that they would consider dropping from future PPU revisions if it would save gates.</div>

